<subSubSection id="C31B51A9CE54A06FFF73FAA9A94735F7" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BBE0222CE54A06FFF73FAA9A94735F7" blockId="36.[151,1437,1361,2034]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">
<emphasis id="B975DE30CE54A06FFF73FAA9AD6B3633" bold="true" box="[151,273,1361,1386]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0179A1CE54A06FFEFDFAA9AD983630" box="[281,482,1361,1385]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirabilis">
<emphasis id="B975DE30CE54A06FFEFDFAA9AD983630" box="[281,482,1361,1385]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Colletes mirabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be assigned to any of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C0179A1CE54A06FFC86FAA9AFC43630" box="[866,958,1361,1385]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975DE30CE54A06FFC86FAA9AFC43630" box="[866,958,1361,1385]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Colletes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-groups. Due the dense yellowishwhite pilosity that covers most of the body in both male and female and its size 
<taxonomicName id="4C0179A1CE54A06FFBEBFA8EA8EE36D4" box="[1039,1172,1397,1421]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirabilis">
<emphasis id="B975DE30CE54A06FFBEBFA8EA8EE36D4" box="[1039,1172,1397,1421]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">C. mirabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
reminds of a species of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C0179A1CE54A06FFF25FA62AD2736E8" box="[193,349,1434,1457]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="squamosus">
<emphasis id="B975DE30CE54A06FFF25FA62AD2736E8" box="[193,349,1434,1457]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">C. squamosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group but the distinct dorsal incision of the male gonocoxite (secondarily fused in all species of the species-groups of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0179A1CE54A06FFE41FA46AE42368C" box="[421,568,1470,1493]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricans">
<emphasis id="B975DE30CE54A06FFE41FA46AE42368C" box="[421,568,1470,1493]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">C. nigricans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0179A1CE54A06FFDAAFA46AE9B368C" box="[590,737,1470,1493]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinatus">
<emphasis id="B975DE30CE54A06FFDAAFA46AE9B368C" box="[590,737,1470,1493]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">C. carinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0179A1CE54A06FFD13FA46AFD6368C" box="[759,940,1469,1493]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hylaeiformis">
<emphasis id="B975DE30CE54A06FFD13FA46AFD6368C" box="[759,940,1469,1493]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">C. hylaeiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0179A1CE54A06FFC27FA46A836368C" box="[963,1100,1470,1493]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caspicus">
<emphasis id="B975DE30CE54A06FFC27FA46A836368C" box="[963,1100,1470,1493]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">C. caspicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0179A1CE54A06FFB77FA46A94D368C" box="[1171,1335,1470,1493]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="squamosus">
<emphasis id="B975DE30CE54A06FFB77FA46A94D368C" box="[1171,1335,1470,1493]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">C. squamosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) clearly contradicts this assumption. Morphologically 
<taxonomicName id="4C0179A1CE54A06FFD40FA1AAF5736A0" box="[676,813,1505,1529]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirabilis">
<emphasis id="B975DE30CE54A06FFD40FA1AAF5736A0" box="[676,813,1505,1529]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">C. mirabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is isolated and the male can easily recognized by the characteristic shape of S 
<number id="3DC91005CE54A06FFE41F9FEADC93547" box="[421,435,1542,1566]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" value="7.0">7</number>
(
<figureCitation id="133A1EA7CE54A06FFE27F9FDAE793547" box="[451,515,1541,1566]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC91005CE54A06FFE12F9FEAE793547" box="[502,515,1542,1566]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
c) and the unique pilosity of the discs of T 
<number id="3DC91005CE54A06FFC3CF9FEA8793547" box="[984,1027,1542,1566]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4</number>
(
<figureCitation id="133A1EA7CE54A06FFBF5F9FDA8293547" box="[1041,1107,1541,1566]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC91005CE54A06FFBA1F9FEA8293547" box="[1093,1107,1542,1566]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
a, b). The discs are free of the thick yellowish-white, appressed appressed hair but instead are densely covered with very fine and short erect hairs that make the discs appear yellowish to greyish while the sculpture of the terga is still visible. This is unique among all 
<taxonomicName id="4C0179A1CE54A06FFF5BF989AD6135D0" box="[191,283,1649,1673]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975DE30CE54A06FFF5BF989AD6135D0" box="[191,283,1649,1673]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Colletes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species known to us. The female is characterized by T 
<number id="3DC91005CE54A06FFC57F98AAFA635D3" box="[947,988,1650,1674]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
densely and completely covered with appressed yellowish-white hairs (
<figureCitation id="133A1EA7CE54A06FFDE9F96DAE2A35F7" box="[525,592,1685,1710]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC91005CE54A06FFDA6F96EAE2A35F7" box="[578,592,1686,1710]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
a, d) and the very large pair of apical clypeal depressions (
<figureCitation id="133A1EA7CE54A06FFB39F96DA96535F7" box="[1245,1311,1685,1710]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC91005CE54A06FFAF5F96DA96535F7" box="[1297,1311,1685,1710]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
b).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31B51A9CE54A06EFF23F941AF7934AC" lastPageId="37" lastPageNumber="438" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BBE0222CE54A06EFF23F941A8783219" blockId="36.[151,1437,1361,2034]" lastBlockId="37.[151,1436,151,320]" lastPageId="37" lastPageNumber="438" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">
<emphasis id="B975DE30CE54A06FFF23F941ADC5358B" bold="true" box="[199,447,1721,1746]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Description. Female.</emphasis>
Bl = 9.5 mm. Head. Head wider than long. Integument black except part of mandible dark reddish-brown. Face except clypeus densely covered with long, yellowish-white, erect hairs, on vertex a bit darker (
<figureCitation id="133A1EA7CE54A06FFF0BF8F9AD483443" box="[239,306,1793,1818]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC91005CE54A06FFEC0F8FAAD483443" box="[292,306,1794,1818]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
a, b). Clypeus flat, without longitudinal median depression, supraclypeal area triangular and convex in profile. Clypeus relatively finely and densely punctate (i = 0.5d), apically coarser and more dispersed; surface between punctures smooth and shiny, large pair of apical clypeal depressions (
<figureCitation id="133A1EA7CE54A06FFBEFF8B1A837343B" box="[1035,1101,1865,1890]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC91005CE54A06FFBDBF8B1A837343B" box="[1087,1101,1865,1890]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
b). Malar area medially about 
<number id="3DC91005CE54A06FFF73F896ACDB34DF" box="[151,161,1902,1926]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DC91005CE54A06FFF4FF896ACC134DF" box="[171,187,1902,1926]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" value="4.0">4</number>
as long as width of mandible base, finely punctate. Antenna black, ventrally dark reddish-brown. Mesosoma. Integument black. Mesoscutal disc impunctate, smooth and shiny. Scutellum largely impunctate, smooth and shiny (
<figureCitation id="133A1EA7CE54A06FFF7BF84DAC9C3497" box="[159,230,1973,1998]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC91005CE54A06FFF3CF84EAC9C3497" box="[216,230,1974,1998]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
c). Mesoscutum, mesepisternum and propodeum densely covered with long light yellowish-white, erect hairs (
<figureCitation id="133A1EA7CE54A06FFF39F821AD5A34AB" box="[221,288,2009,2034]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC91005CE54A06FFEF6F822AD5A34AB" box="[274,288,2010,2034]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
a, c). Wings. Very slightly yellowish; wing venation yellowish-brown. Legs. Integument black to dark reddish-brown. Vestiture whitish to yellowish-white, scopa white. Metasoma. Integument black except depressed apical tergal margins reddish to yellowish translucent (
<figureCitation id="133A1EA7CE55A06EFCC6FF44AF10338C" box="[802,874,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC91005CE55A06EFCB8FF44AF10338C" box="[860,874,188,213]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
d). T 
<number id="3DC91005CE55A06EFC4CFF44AFAA338D" box="[936,976,188,212]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
densely covered with short appressed, yellowish hairs, on T 
<number id="3DC91005CE55A06EFE6CFF18ADE833A1" box="[392,402,224,248]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="1.0">1</number>
additionally with a few long, erect yellowish-white hairs; apical tergal hair bands broad but mostly indistinguishable from discs; terga apically slightly but distinctly depressed (
<figureCitation id="133A1EA7CE55A06EFBBBFEFCA8DE3244" box="[1119,1188,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC91005CE55A06EFB72FEFCA8DE3244" box="[1174,1188,260,285]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
d). Terga densely and very finely punctate (i &lt;0.5d), between punctures smooth and shiny (
<figureCitation id="133A1EA7CE55A06EFC46FEDFAF9E3219" box="[930,996,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC91005CE55A06EFC32FEDFAF9E3219" box="[982,996,295,320]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
d).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF7E52AACE55A06EFF73FA70AEAA36E4" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" targetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" targetPageId="37">
<paragraph id="8BBE0222CE55A06EFF73FA70AEAA36E4" blockId="37.[151,1435,1416,1469]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">
<emphasis id="B975DE30CE55A06EFF73FA70AD6936C7" bold="true" box="[151,275,1416,1438]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">FIGURE 8.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0179A1CE55A06EFEFEFA70AE8E36C7" authority="Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin" authorityName="Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin" box="[282,756,1416,1438]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirabilis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B975DE30CE55A06EFEFEFA70ADB536C7" box="[282,463,1416,1438]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">Colletes mirabilis</emphasis>
Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A246634BCE55A06EFD1FFA70AF3636C7" box="[763,844,1416,1438]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B975DE30CE55A06EFD1FFA70AF3636C7" bold="true" box="[763,844,1416,1438]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BBE0222CE55A06EFF23FA1CAF7934AC" blockId="37.[151,1437,1508,2037]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">
<collectingCountry id="F31642B2CE55A06EFF23FA1CAD7E36A4" box="[199,260,1508,1533]" name="Malta" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">Male</collectingCountry>
. Bl = 8.5 mm. Head. Head wider than long. Integument black except part of mandible dark reddishbrown. Face densely covered with long, yellowish-white, erect hairs. Malar area medially about 
<number id="3DC91005CE55A06EFB1DF9F1A97E3578" box="[1273,1284,1545,1569]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DC91005CE55A06EFAEAF9F1A9663578" box="[1294,1308,1545,1569]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="3.0">3</number>
as long as width of mandible base, finely striate. Antenna black, ventrally dark brown. Mesosoma. Integument black. Mesoscutal disc between punctures smooth and shiny; disc sparsely punctate (i = 1.5–2.0d) with small punctures. Scutellum anteriorly impunctate but with dense punctation apically, surface smooth and shiny. Mesoscutum, scutellum, metanotum, mesepisternum and propodeum covered with long, yellowish-white erect hairs (
<figureCitation id="133A1EA7CE55A06EFADEF960A90535E8" box="[1338,1407,1688,1713]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC91005CE55A06EFA95F961A90535E8" box="[1393,1407,1689,1713]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
a). Wings. Slightly yellowish-brown; wing venation yellowish-brown. Legs. Integument black, base and tips of tibias and barsitarsi reddish-brown and other tarsomeres yellowish-brown. Vestiture white. Metasoma. Integument black except depressed apical tergal margins reddish to yellowish translucent (
<figureCitation id="133A1EA7CE55A06EFC1AF8FCA83D3444" box="[1022,1095,1796,1821]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC91005CE55A06EFBDDF8FCA83D3444" box="[1081,1095,1796,1821]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
b). T 
<number id="3DC91005CE55A06EFB6CF8FDA8E83444" box="[1160,1170,1797,1821]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="1.0">1</number>
densely covered with yellowish-white short appressed hairs and with much longer erect hairs; discs of T 
<number id="3DC91005CE55A06EFBA4F8D1A8103418" box="[1088,1130,1833,1857]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4</number>
densely covered with very fine and short erect hairs that make the discs appear yellowish to greyish while the sculpture of the terga is still visible; rest of terga densely covered with short appressed yellowish-white hairs (
<figureCitation id="133A1EA7CE55A06EFBD0F888A80234D0" box="[1076,1144,1904,1929]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC91005CE55A06EFB8EF888A80234D0" box="[1130,1144,1904,1929]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
b); apical tergal hair band on T 
<number id="3DC91005CE55A06EFF30F86DACA434F4" box="[212,222,1941,1965]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="1.0">1</number>
narrow, on following terga broad but irregularly shaped (
<figureCitation id="133A1EA7CE55A06EFC7CF86CAF9A34F4" box="[920,992,1940,1965]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC91005CE55A06EFC36F86CAF9A34F4" box="[978,992,1940,1965]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
b). Terga apically deeply and sharply depressed. Terga with very dense and fine punctation (i &lt;0.5d), between punctures smooth and shiny (
<figureCitation id="133A1EA7CE55A06EFADDF840A9043488" box="[1337,1406,1976,2001]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC91005CE55A06EFA94F840A9043488" box="[1392,1406,1976,2001]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
b). Terminalia. Genitalia and S 
<number id="3DC91005CE55A06EFE2EF825ADA234AC" box="[458,472,2013,2037]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="7.0">7</number>
as illustrated (
<figureCitation id="133A1EA7CE55A06EFD99F824AEB334AC" box="[637,713,2012,2037]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,364,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[151,1436,363,1395]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 8. Colletes mirabilis Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin sp. nov., female: a. specimen, lateral view; b. head; c. scutum and scutellum; d. metasomal terga 1 and 2. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248254/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">
Figs. 
<number id="3DC91005CE55A06EFD58F824AEB334AC" box="[700,713,2012,2037]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
c–d).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
